JOHANNESBURG – Cricket South Africa (CSA) on Friday paid tribute to late former communications department member Chris Day. He served as a member of the communications team for a long period before he became a special adviser to then CSA Chief Executive officer (CEO) Dr Ali Bacher. CSA did not give details surrounding Day’s death, except to say that he died on Wednesday. “Chris played a key role in getting our administration off to a sound start immediately after unity, working close both with Ali Bacher and Gerald Majola,” CSA Acting CEO Thabang Moroe said. READ: CSA to probe alleged racial abuse of Imran Tahir during fourth ODI “On behalf of the CSA Family, I extend our deepest condolences to his family, friends and associates.” His funeral service will take place on Tuesday at the Methodist Church in Port Alfred in the Eastern Cape. eNCA